  <source>Office of Rare Diseases (ORD)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES: I. Assess pituitary size and anatomic configuration by magnetic resonance imaging
      (MRI) in 4 affected dwarfs in the province of Sindh, Pakistan.

      II. Evaluate ultradian growth hormone (GH) secretory patterns in 4 affected dwarfs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE: Pituitary size and anatomy and growth hormone response are evaluated.

      All patients undergo MRI of the pituitary fossa on day 1. On day 2, homozygous patients
      receive a slow infusion of normal saline with blood sampling every 10 minutes.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
